question:
Background: There are 3 types of District: College Town, Senior Living Community, and Dormitory District.
There are 2 types of Supermarkets: Fairway Market, and Walmart.
There are 2 types of Product: Cookies, and Canned Pumpkin.
Each College Town has Walmart and Fairway Market.
Each Senior Living Community has Walmart and Fairway Market.
Each Dormitory District has Fairway Market and Walmart.
Each Fairway Market has Canned Pumpkin and Cookies.
Each Walmart has Cookies and Canned Pumpkin.
The number of each Fairway Market 's Canned Pumpkin equals each Dormitory District 's Fairway Market.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Fairway Market equals 11.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Walmart equals 13.
The number of each College Town 's Walmart equals the sum of each Senior Living Community 's Fairway Market and each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Walmart 's Canned Pumpkin equals 5 more than the sum of each Senior Living Community 's Fairway Market, each Senior Living Community 's Walmart, and each College Town 's Walmart.
The number of each College Town 's Fairway Market equals 1 more than each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Walmart 's Cookies equals 7 more than the sum of each Senior Living Community 's Fairway Market, each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets, and each College Town 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Walmart equals 5 times each Dormitory District 's Fairway Market.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Fairway Market equals 10 more than each Senior Living Community 's Walmart.
The number of each Fairway Market 's Cookies equals 6 times the sum of each Walmart 's Product, each College Town 's Supermarkets, and each College Town 's Walmart.
How many Cookies does Fairway Market have?
solution:
Define each Senior Living Community 's Walmart as f; So f = 13.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Fairway Market as p; So p = 10 + f = 10 + 13 = 0.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets as o; So o = f + p = 13 + 0 = 13.
Define each College Town 's Fairway Market as W; So W = 1 + o = 1 + 13 = 14.
Define each College Town 's Walmart as Q; So Q = p + o = 0 + 13 = 13.
Define each College Town 's Supermarkets as B; So B = Q + W = 13 + 14 = 4.
Define each Walmart 's Cookies as c; w = p + o = 0 + 13 = 13; o = B + w = 4 + 13 = 17; So c = 7 + o = 7 + 17 = 1.
Define each Walmart 's Canned Pumpkin as m; p = f + Q = 13 + 13 = 3; Y = p + p = 3 + 3 = 6; So m = 5 + Y = 5 + 6 = 11.
Define each Walmart 's Product as v; So v = c + m = 1 + 11 = 12.
Define each Fairway Market 's Cookies as O; V = Q + B = 13 + 4 = 17; r = v + V = 12 + 17 = 6; So O = 6 * r = 6 * 6 = 13.
